Use Arch-standard runtime paths in the systemd unit.

Upstream ships /usr/sbin and /var/run; Arch uses /usr/bin and /run.
Also let systemd create /run/ndppd via RuntimeDirectory= so the pidfile
directory exists on a fresh boot (ndppd does not create it itself).

--- a/ndppd.service
+++ b/ndppd.service
@@ -5,5 +5,6 @@
 [Service]
-ExecStart=/usr/sbin/ndppd -d -p /var/run/ndppd/ndppd.pid
+ExecStart=/usr/bin/ndppd -d -p /run/ndppd/ndppd.pid
 Type=forking
-PIDFile=/var/run/ndppd/ndppd.pid
+PIDFile=/run/ndppd/ndppd.pid
+RuntimeDirectory=ndppd

